# OctoAcme Personas

This document defines typical roles and responsibilities used in OctoAcme project docs and exercises.

---

## Developers

### Role Summary
Developers design, build, test, and deliver software components. They collaborate with product and project leads to implement features that meet acceptance criteria and quality standards.

### Responsibilities
- Implement features and fixes to meet acceptance criteria
- Write and maintain tests and documentation
- Participate in design and code reviews
- Assist in estimating and planning work
- Help identify technical risks and propose mitigations

### Goals
- Deliver reliable, maintainable code
- Reduce cycle time from idea to production
- Maintain high test coverage and observability

### Typical Communication
- Daily standups and sprint planning
- PR descriptions and code review comments
- Technical design docs when needed

---

## Product Managers

### Role Summary
Product Managers define what should be built to deliver customer and business value. They own the product vision, prioritize the backlog, and measure outcomes.

### Responsibilities
- Define problem statements and success metrics
- Prioritize the roadmap and backlog
- Collaborate with stakeholders and engineering on trade-offs
- Validate solutions through user research and metrics

### Goals
- Maximize customer value and impact
- Make clear, data-driven prioritization decisions
- Ensure product-market fit and usability

### Typical Communication
- Weekly alignment with PM and engineering leads
- Roadmap updates and stakeholder briefings
- Acceptance criteria and feature specs

---

## Project Managers

### Role Summary
Project Managers coordinate delivery activities, manage schedules, risks, and communications. They enable the team to deliver on commitments efficiently.

### Responsibilities
- Create and maintain project plans and timelines
- Manage risks, dependencies, and resource constraints
- Facilitate meetings (kickoff, planning, retrospectives)
- Ensure consistent project documentation and status reporting
- Coordinate cross-team and stakeholder communication

### Goals
- Deliver projects on time and within scope
- Minimize unplanned work and escalations
- Maintain transparency and alignment across stakeholders

### Typical Communication
- Weekly status updates and stakeholder reports
- Risk registers and decision logs
- Coordination via project boards and meeting facilitation

---

## Quality Assurance Lead

### Role Summary
The Quality Assurance Lead owns quality strategy, develops and maintains test plans, and coordinates test execution activities. They ensure that all deliverables meet acceptance criteria and quality standards before release.

### Responsibilities
- Define QA strategy and test approach for the project
- Develop and maintain test plans and test cases
- Coordinate manual and automated testing efforts
- Perform triage of defects and track resolution
- Ensure Definition of Done is met before features move to release
- Validate acceptance criteria across deliverables

### Goals
- Prevent defects from reaching production
- Maintain high quality standards and customer satisfaction
- Reduce rework and post-release issues
- Enable fast, confident releases

### Interactions
- **With Developers:** Collaborates on test automation, acceptance criteria clarity, and bug triage
- **With Product Manager:** Aligns on acceptance criteria and quality expectations
- **With Project Manager:** Tracks QA progress, identifies blockers, and ensures quality milestones are met
- **With Release Manager:** Provides sign-off on quality readiness for release Go/No-Go decisions
- **With UX Designer:** Validates user experience and usability against design specifications

### Typical Communication
- Sprint planning and backlog refinement
- Daily standup participation and issue triage
- QA progress reports and quality metrics
- Test case documentation and defect logs

---

## Release Manager

### Role Summary
The Release Manager owns the end-to-end release process, schedules releases, coordinates deployment activities, and manages release communications. They ensure smooth transitions from development to production with minimal risk.

### Responsibilities
- Create and communicate release schedules and timelines
- Prepare release notes and deployment documentation
- Coordinate with development and QA for Go/No-Go decisions
- Oversee deployment activities and post-deployment verification
- Manage rollback and incident response procedures
- Track and communicate release status to stakeholders
- Document lessons learned and improve release processes

### Goals
- Execute reliable, predictable releases
- Minimize deployment risks and downtime
- Ensure transparent communication with all stakeholders
- Establish repeatable, efficient release processes

### Interactions
- **With Developers:** Coordinates final code reviews, merges, and deployment preparation
- **With Quality Assurance Lead:** Confirms quality readiness and test completion before release
- **With Project Manager:** Aligns on release timeline and coordinates with project milestones
- **With Product Manager:** Communicates feature readiness and supports release announcements
- **With Stakeholders:** Provides release updates, deployment windows, and post-release summaries

### Typical Communication
- Release planning meetings and deployment windows
- Release notes and deployment checklists
- Incident response coordination
- Stakeholder release bulletins

---

## UX Designer

### Role Summary
The UX Designer ensures that products are intuitive, usable, and delightful. They advocate for the end-user perspective throughout the project lifecycle and validate that solutions meet usability standards.

### Responsibilities
- Define user interface (UI) and user experience (UX) requirements
- Create wireframes, prototypes, and design specifications
- Conduct user research and usability testing
- Validate features against design specifications
- Collaborate on accessibility and inclusive design standards
- Provide design assets and guidelines to development team
- Iterate on designs based on user feedback and metrics

### Goals
- Deliver usable, accessible, and delightful user experiences
- Reduce user friction and support burden
- Maximize user adoption and satisfaction
- Ensure consistency across the product

### Interactions
- **With Product Manager:** Collaborates on feature requirements and user research to inform prioritization
- **With Developers:** Partners during implementation to ensure design fidelity and technical feasibility
- **With Quality Assurance Lead:** Validates usability testing and user acceptance
- **With Stakeholders:** Presents design rationale and gathers feedback
- **With Technical Writer:** Ensures UI/UX documentation and help content align with design

### Typical Communication
- Design reviews and feedback sessions
- Wireframes and design specifications
- Usability test reports and findings
- Design system documentation

---

## Technical Writer

### Role Summary
The Technical Writer maintains product and process documentation, creates release notes, and supports onboarding. They ensure that information is clear, accurate, and accessible to all audiences.

### Responsibilities
- Create and maintain internal process documentation
- Develop user-facing product documentation and help content
- Prepare release notes and migration guides
- Support team onboarding with clear guides and runbooks
- Review and edit project and technical documentation for clarity
- Maintain documentation standards and templates
- Ensure documentation stays current with product changes

### Goals
- Reduce support burden through clear self-service documentation
- Accelerate team onboarding and knowledge sharing
- Maintain single source of truth for processes and procedures
- Support product adoption through excellent user documentation

### Interactions
- **With All Roles:** Gathers information and feedback to ensure comprehensive, accurate documentation
- **With Developers:** Documents technical architecture, APIs, and deployment procedures
- **With Product Manager:** Creates user-facing documentation and help content aligned with feature announcements
- **With Quality Assurance Lead:** Documents test procedures and acceptance criteria
- **With Release Manager:** Prepares release notes and deployment documentation
- **With UX Designer:** Ensures help content and UI labels align with design specifications

### Typical Communication
- Documentation planning and review meetings
- Style guide and template maintenance
- Documentation drafts and feedback cycles
- Onboarding and knowledge base articles

---

## How these personas are used in the exercise
- Use these persona definitions to frame scenarios and sample interactions in the Skills Exercise.
- Each persona can be used as a persona prompt for Copilot Spaces to shape role-specific guidance.
- When creating projects, assign team members to roles based on their skills and project needs.